  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; 7 are formally assessed and 6 are flagged as epistemic gaps. The intended use scope — regulatory submission support for a Class III implantable VAD operating at 5 L/min, 2500 RPM, targeting plasma-free hemoglobin predictions within ±15% of bench measurements — is described only in the Claim and Requirement prose. No structured hasContextOfUse node is linked from this UnitOfAssurance, constituting the targeted W-ON-01 ontological gap.",
