    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD conditions is formally accepted as a complete ASME V&V 40 package submission. All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated: 7 factors are assessed with documented gaps between achieved and required levels, and 6 factors are designated not-assessed epistemic gaps at MRL 5. The package is accepted as a complete record of the current credibility posture; the decision does not imply that the model is fit for regulatory submission, but that the assessment process has been faithfully executed and documented. The intended use scope — absolute hemolysis prediction for a Class III VAD at 5 L/min and 2500 RPM — is described in the bound Claim and Requirement nodes. No structured Context of Use node is linked at the UnitOfAssurance level under the Minimal profile.",
